---
import Slide from "../components/Slide.astro";
---

<Slide>
	<h2>What I learned</h2>
	<ul class="learnings">
		<li class="fragment">
			🧩 <strong>Use existing small models</strong> for specialized tasks — a few MB of landmarker beats training
			anything yourself
		</li>
		<li class="fragment">
			📊 <strong>The more training data, the better</strong> — the fingerspelling demo lives and dies by its recorded
			samples
		</li>
		<li class="fragment">
			⚡ In the age of AI, coming up with a <strong>fun working demo took less time than I expected</strong>
		</li>
	</ul>
	<aside class="notes">
		Wrap-up before Q&A: the heavy lifting was already done by MediaPipe's pretrained models; our own "ML" is a kNN over
		samples recorded in five minutes; and the whole deck came together surprisingly fast.
	</aside>
</Slide>

<style>
	.learnings {
		list-style: none;
		margin: 0.8em auto 0;
		padding: 0;
		max-width: 85%;
		text-align: left;
		font-size: 0.7em;

		li {
			margin: 0.9em 0;
		}
	}
</style>
